===Etymology===
From {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|abracadabra}}, a word used in magical writings, of uncertain origin. Relationships have been suggested with {{term|Abraxas}} (a Gnostic deity), and with various Aramaic or Hebrew terms ({{m|arc|עַבְדָא כְּדַברָא|sc=Hebr}}, ''avda kedavara''; “what was said has been done”; {{m|he|עבראכדברא|sc=Hebr}}, ''avra kedavra''; “what has said has come to pass”; {{m|he|ארבע-אחד-ארבע|sc=Hebr}} when it is read from right to left [http://www.scribd.com/doc/14656725/Abracadabra]), but there is little supporting evidence.

